OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FThree ethical issues around
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fpig heart transplants      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A US man has become the world's first  
OL,6, person to get a heart transplant from a
OL,7, genetically modified pig.              
OL,9,F57-year-old David Bennett, who doctors 
OL,10,Fsay was too ill to qualify for a human 
OL,11,Fheart, is doing well three days after  
OL,12,Fthe experimental seven-hour treatment. 
OL,14,FThe surgery is being hailed by many as 
OL,15,Fa medical breakthrough that could      
OL,16,Fshorten transplant waiting times and   
OL,17,Fchange the lives of patients around the
OL,18,Fworld. But some are questioning if the 
OL,19,Fprocedure can be ethically justified.  
